title: League of legends Editor
body:
Hi 
I am looking for an editor that can help me start a youtube channel. Contact me on the league or write me on icarrythecarry93@gmail.com.
We will discuss more what I need.

replies.body: really 50$ for hour looks a lot. especially for a new account.  do people earn that much on youtube lol?

> [{quoted}](name=SupportGlory,realm=EUW,application-id=EBBIvmVK,discussion-id=hYU8FztL,comment-id=0001,timestamp=2019-01-06T13:37:07.950+0000)
>
> really 50$ for hour looks a lot. especially for a new account.  do people earn that much on youtube lol?

It has nothing to do with how much you'll make on YT (which will be zero until you hit 4000 watch hours per year with 1000 subscribers) and everything to do with how much a skilled freelancing video editor will expect to be paid for their time.
yeah but I am actually for a normal editor. not really a bunny fufu editor lol

> [{quoted}](name=SupportGlory,realm=EUW,application-id=EBBIvmVK,discussion-id=hYU8FztL,comment-id=000100000000,timestamp=2019-01-06T14:11:57.763+0000)
>
> yeah but I am actually for a normal editor. not really a bunny fufu editor lol

I don't know what you mean by that, but time is time, and professionals expect to be paid for the time they put into a client's project. If you have more time than money, consider doing some basic editing on your own.

You'd have more luck if you put out an ad for editing services on a freelancing website. If you don't want to pay a contractor probably $50+/hour, you could look up some tutorials and try your hand at doing some basic editing on your own.
